olive oil
1 carrot
½ Onion
1 courgette
1 packet Pork Mince
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet barbecue seasoning
½ packet passata
1 packet Baby Leaves
⅓ cup water
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
20 g butter
1 packet filo pastry
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Grate carrot. Thinly slice onion (see ingredients). Slice courgette into half-moons.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add carrot and leek and cook until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic paste, barbecue seasoning and  passata (see ingredients) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add baby leaves and the water, then stir until wilted, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the filling looks too thick.

• Transfer pork filling to a baking dish and evenly sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• In a small microwave-safe bowl, add the butter and microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and place on top of filling to completely cover.
• Gently brush melted butter over to coat and sprinkle over mixed sesame seeds. Bake pie until golden, 15-20 minutes.

• Divide BBQ pork filo pie with Cheddar cheese between bowls. Enjoy!